      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nBefore this patch can land I need to remove the \"fortestonly\" tag.\n\nNote that I still get a crash in null_alloc_rs() if I enable memory allocation failures via \"lctl set_param alloc_fail_rate=0.1\" (or similar).  The change there so far was only the addition of debugging in the LASSERTF().  That isn't the core issue of this patch, so it would otherwise be fine to land after fixing the overly-optimistic comment that reports fixing this problem.",
