          "date": "2012-08-06 22:11:18.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-1387 lvfs: print message on allocation failure",
        "message": "LU-1387 lvfs: print message on allocation failure\n\nBack in commit ca6dd9a48e7b3ebf5df8a78c8ed65f7676cebf4d (b=12211),\nthe introduction of the \"conditionally fail allocations\" feature\ncause the printing of error messages on the console for memory\nallocation failures to be accidentally disabled.  This was a result\nof subtle boolean/precedence changes, and not intentional.\n\nReinstate the printing of console errors on allocation failures\nwith an improved format that prints the actual location instead\nof obd_alloc_fail().\n\nDuring testing of the conditional memory allocation failure code,\nthere were several LASSERT() failures in null_alloc_rs().  While\nthe core bug was not yet fixed, improve the LASSERT() verbosity for\ndebugging any problem hit there in the future.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I4ea2b93d2b11869940d687babd2eeafd08ca500c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
